		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_5" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD>The Battle for Lego Universe<BR />Book One: The Beginning of the End<BR />Chapter 47<BR />A Daring Rescue<BR /><BR />The Infection Ray never touched Dusty Holster. Instead, he was blasted straight through the fog and into Sky’s face, causing her to fall to the ledge below.<BR />“Whoa!” Kit Wanderware yelled as he leaped away from her. “You could have crushed me! Why didn’t you warn me?”<BR />But Sky was just as puzzled as he was. What had just happened… and more, what the Spider Boss had said… about a secret base…<BR />Dusty Holster screamed. Patches of Maelstrom covered his body where the webs had scorched him and the Maelstrom fog and infected most of his legs, head, and arms. It wasn’t enough to turn him into the Stromling, but Sky could tell from his moaning that it was enough to smash him. <BR />But then she heard someone yell. And the yell was very familiar. Too familiar. <BR />The clang of a large metal object reverberated around the Monument as the first Spiderling went screeching down to the ground. Three more joined the first one before the Minifigure leaped out of the fog, the Spider Boss missing every blow with its gun and smashing many Spiderlings. It was Rusty Steele. <BR />“What are you doing!?” Sky screamed in both terror and in joy. <BR />“Saving the Universe!” He cried back, his Thinking Cap appearing from nowhere and landing on his head. “It’s been a while since I did this…” He murmured to himself.<BR />Rusty’s hands began to glow blue with Imagination energy, and bricks swirled around him from an unknown source. Then they began building around him.<BR />The moment the Maelstrom fog parted, the moment the Spider Boss’ blood red eyes noticed the valiant Minifigures, the moment it pointed its massive gun at the valiant Minifigures… the Personal Fortress blasted it backwards with a series if rapid shots. <BR />“Whoa!” Kit and Sky cried in unison, leaping out if the building’s way as the Spider Boss screeched in pain. But a simple Personal Fortress might be a terror to a hoard of Ronin, but it was nothing to the queen of all arachnids.<BR />In seconds, the Fortress had been smashed and Rusty had been knocked to the Monument’s hand. He slipped, and grabbed into one of the two, stone fingers for dear life. <BR />The Spider Boss crawled down from the half smashed head and onto the shoulder, hissing evilly. Then Kit Wanderware and Sky Lane showed the power of the Venture League…<BR />Both of them burst into blue flame and leaped onto the spider’s head. Kit back flipped and buried his spear into one of its eyes, causing it to stand up on two, pointed legs and scream. Maelstrom fog blasted from every pore in its body, and the menacing purple wisps licked at the two Venture Leaguers. Sky fired her flareguns madly as Kit swiped his spear. But they were no match for the fog…<BR />The whip suddenly lassoed Sky by the throat, pulling her down from her perch on the Spider Boss’ head. Kit soon followed.<BR />And then Dusty fell to the ground, unconscious, a whip in his scorched hand.<BR />Sky smiled. “I’ve never seen him do that before!”<BR />But there was no time for chatting. The Spider Boss was nearing Rusty by the second…<BR />But the gang of freedom fighters was once again halted by yet another surprise: the sound of a Wormholer firing. <BR />“Go back to where you belong, Arachnid of Chaos! Go to the Land of the Smashed! And stay there!” Madison Growl roared, leaping in front of the giant spider just where the stone arm of the Monument bent. <BR />“NO!” Sky cried. Sure, she was glad the Paradox Space Marauder was alive, but she’d rather see her fall of a cliff then die at the hands of the Spider Boss. Well, the Spider Boss was the one who pushed her off the cliff in the first place… but… whatever. <BR />But Madison didn’t flinch. Instead, she grabbed something from her large shoulderpads. It was a small, metallic, black stick with a curved, red brick on top: A Maelstrom Ball. She tossed this as the Spider Boss, causing a massive explosion that made the stone arm lurch. <BR />The Spider Boss then aimed it gun and fired at Madison, multiple rapidly shot bullets blasting towards her at an impossible speed.<BR />But the bullets never hit her.<BR />A wave of bricks had appeared in front of her, protecting her from the blasts. She turned and saw Rusty Steele with a concentrated expression and sweat forming on his brow. He was holding out his hands, using his Imagination to make bricks materialize from his invisible bag. He then waved his arm, and the bricks connected to make a wall.<BR />The wall was smashed in mere seconds, and was replaced by the massive torrent on a fully charged Infection Ray. <BR />But this time it was Sky’s turn to save the day. Well… save the second. She pulled a flaregun from Kit’s hand (Hers didn’t have a grappling hook), and leaped for the two Minifigures, knocking them clean off the arm of the Monument. <BR />As the stone hand crumpled, the three brave Minifigures of the Nexus Force fell. Sky Lane then grabbed Madison and Rusty tightly and shot a hook up at the arm. They swing back and forth for a few minutes, then began to climb.<BR />Until the rope snapped. </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />THIS IS INTENESE!!!!<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />CB</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />Thanks! The next chapter will be REALLY intense. Mind if I tell you the name of the chapter? <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />SPOILER ALERT!!!!!!! <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR />It will be called "The Fall of the Spider Boss". Intense, eh? <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />~Kahangkrack~
                
            
			
