		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_10" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD>AUTHORS NOTE: This is my longest and most intense chapter yet! Enjoy!!! <img class="emoticon emoticon-smile" id="smile" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/smile.png" alt="Smile" title="Smile" /><BR /><BR />The Battle for Lego Universe<BR />Book One: The Beginning of the End<BR />Chapter 48<BR />The Fall of the Spider Boss<BR /><BR />Wind rushed past Sky’s face as she, Madison, and Rusty fell to their dooms. She couldn’t believe what was happening. She was going to be smashed. <BR />Then she landed with a crash and lost consciousness.<BR />Madison sighed. “Thanks for the extra ledge!” She said to Rusty, who had hastily built a platform to block their fall. <BR />“You’re very welcome!” He smiled, wiping the sweat from his brow with shivering hands. <BR />“Now, let’s get to the ledge located a few inches below, shall we? Before this wobbly one breaks.”<BR />Rusty looked heart-broken. <BR />The Space Marauder grabbed the flaregun from Sky Lane, inserted a new grappling hook, and fired upwards. “Staying down here is dangerous. And I want to see who or what caused our rope to break.”<BR />In moments, they were climbing up the steep cliff that lead to the Launch Area. “Leave Sky!” Madison yelled. “She can find her way up, and, at the moment, this is urgent!” <BR />Soon afterwards, they were on top, staring at the wreckage. Everything had been shattered except the three lucky launchpads in that area: The Nimbus Station Pad, the Block Yard Pad, and the Avant Grove Pad. <BR />Madison spun around to look at a mildly hidden valley. She ran there but only saw the scorched remains of trees and… and the bricks of buffalo pets. “They didn’t deserve this…” She whispered as a tear dribbled down her cheek. She pulled off her visor-less helmet and walked away, tossing it behind her as she went.<BR />Rusty rushed towards her. “Only the launchpads survived! Even the booths and picnic pats have been destroyed! I can’t find anyone… I’m afraid they’ve been smashed too…”<BR />“No! They can’t have been… no…”<BR />The Forman put his arm around her shuddering shoulder. “It’s okay. We’re alive.”<BR />He was slapped so hard that he almost fell back off the remains of the Assembly Bridge and back down to his doom.<BR />“WE’RE ALIVE!!?? WE’RE ALIVE!!?? What kind of thing is that to say!!?? No wonder you joined Assembly! You are always at the back on the army… you cowards need to build things to keep yourself safe and “to help others”! But you only save yourselves! COWARD!” Madison slammed her Wormholer into the ground and fell to her knees, sobbing. <BR />No one had ever seen anyone from Paradox cry. They were always the most serious of the lot. They were thought to be cold blooded, emotionless, and un-trustworthy. That’s why the rest of the Nexus Force didn’t exactly “like” them. They thought the Maelstrom could be used for good, and shouldn’t be destroyed.<BR />Assembly had already proved that wrong, and Venture and Paradox were in charge of stopping it. All Vanda Darkflame’s work was… not approved for at all. <BR />Suddenly, Madison looked up, her face streaked with tear-lines. She stood up, yanked the Wormholer from the ground, and pulled the rope off the flaregun so that Sky could get up when she regained consciousness. <BR />“Uhhh… Madison? Madison??? Where ARE you going???”<BR />She looked back at him. “For three years, I have been held captive with the Maelstrom. For three years, I have suffered endlessly. Then I escape… and a couple of second later, Wisp Lee is captured. We escape together, and face multiple hardships. Then, Silas picks us up and helps us. Do you see the pattern? The rest of the Nexus Force doesn’t care about what’s right. Paradox can only rely on Paradox. And now, both Silas and Wisp have been smashed, and the world is crumbling around me. Unlike you, I don’t care for the fall of the Maelstrom. I care for the survival of the Nexus Force.” <BR />And then she leaped off the cliff, firing the flaregun’s last grappling hook at the Monument. <BR />Rusty sat back down. “What have I done?”<BR />**************************************************<wbr />*******************************************<BR />Kit Wanderware grabbed at Dusty Holster’s limp body, dragging him down one ledge and away from the malevolent eyes of the Spider Boss. <BR />The Spider screeched, vowing vengeance for the escape of the three Nexus Force members, and then began searching for the two that remained.<BR />Kit sat huddled against the boulders, his hand on Dusty’s head, feeling for anything wrong. He then placed his hand in the cowboy’s temple, feeling for pulse. His heart was still pumping, and pumping just like it usually did. Then, all of a sudden, a Spiderling scuttled past him, barely missing glaring at him and reporting him. But something was strange about this Spiderling… it only had three eyes. <BR />The Dark Spiderling Invader scuttled towards the right shoulder of the Monument, then began chirping on some terrible, Maelstrom language. <BR />The Spider Boss replied in a horribly chilling voice: “Ah, the General is ready for his first assault? Good. Very good. Tell all my Spiderlings to go down to his camp, and tell them they will be smashed if they hesitate.”<BR />The Dark Spiderling ran back down the arm of the Monument, and then shot a web to its waist. It continued until it got to the bottom of the massive statue of the half wreaked, plain Minifigure attacking the massive, skeletal statue. <BR />Kit looked down. “This is bad. This is really bad. Everyone in the picnic area won’t be able to withstand the full force of every Spiderling, Stromling, and Mech on this world. And then there’s this “General” figure…”<BR />But then, the unimaginable happened: The hoard of Spiderlings began to swarm up the Monument. He was to be caught for sure! But weren’t they told to go to the “general”?<BR />But the army of Dark Spiderling Invaders passed him without a glance. A few stared at him for a moment, hissed, then continued. He couldn’t make head or tail of what was happening.<BR />But then the Spider Boss spoke. “What is this? I told you to go help the General!”<BR />The Spiderlings began to chirp, then, strangely, the one that had been spoken to just before spoke so that Kit could understand it.<BR />“You ordered me to order them to do it, under pain of death. I thought I would just order them to kill you… under pain of death!”<BR />The red light of the Spider Boss’ eyes could be seen even where Kit was sitting.<BR />“You are Maelstrom! You cannot go against me!”<BR />Kit Wanderware climbed up the head to peek at what was happening just in time: The Spiderling Scout’s purple and black hide burst, revealing a red and black Spiderling. A Paradox Spiderling. “Kill her.” It said, and they all shot the Spider Boss in unison.<BR />**************************************************<wbr />*******************************************<BR />Madison Growl swing up to the arm just as it happened. A hoard of Spiderling atop the head of the Monument rapidly fired at the Spider Boss, who was screeching at the shoulder. She couldn’t understand it one bit. <BR />But almost every projectile bounced off her almost impenetrable hide. Maelstrom fog poured from every pore in her body, and Maelstrom goo sprouted from every place she stepped. <BR />Suddenly, the Spider Boss leaped upwards, slamming down into the head of the Monument with so much force that it smashed at least 500 Spiderlings. She then began rapidly firing at them, smashing 100 more with ease, and obliterating many more with the constant, burning jets from her flamethrower. <BR />Madison couldn’t believe the power that drove the First Stromling. This beast couldn’t leave Avant Gardens. It would conquer all of Lego Universe in a flash. <BR />But what had turned the Spiderlings against the Boss?<BR />After almost a thousand Spiderlings had been smashed, the Spider Boss roared from within the fog. “Join me again! Or all of you will be smashed!!!”<BR />The Dark Spiderling Invaders re-joined the Maelstrom in seconds, and the Paradox Spiderling was smashed. Wait… a PARADOX Spiderling? Madison couldn’t understand anything one bit. <BR />“ALL OF YOU!” The Queen of all Spiders roared. “GO DOWN TO THE GENERAL AND HELP HIM IN HIS CAUSE!!!” <BR />In moments, the Spiderlings had scuttled back down the Monument like a hoard of thousands and thousands of shadowy elephants, causing what looked like a “stampede”. <BR />Then, for absolutely no reason, mind took over matter and Madison Growl leaped into the head of the Monument, firing her Wormholer at the beast’s belly. <BR />The Spider Boss looked down at her quizzically, and what looked like a smile crossed its mouth-less face. <BR />Madison bolted. Bolted for her life and everything she held dear. She leaped off the Monument’s head and landed on the left arm, running faster than she had ever run before. The Spider Boss shot at her, missing by centimeters and taking out Madison’s Wormholer instead of her entire body. The weapon spiraled down the great fall down, still shooting. The trigger must have been jammed. <BR />The Space Marauder was just about to reach the Monument’s hand to climb up the sword it held when a massive, sizzling, orange web slammed in front of her and blocked her escape. The Spider Boss then began pulled with the web, and the arm began to slowly break, being pulled closer and closer to the giant arachnid. <BR />Purple steam vented from two of the piped on its back… as it got ready to fire two, massive homing missiles. The torpedoes blasted from their holsters, spun around in mid-air, and rocketed towards Madison. She closed her eyes, knowing that this was the end. She was going to join her two other, valiant Paradox friends. <BR />But then, everything happened far too fast. A massive blast on Maelstrom energy knocked Madison off the arm of the Monument and onto the sword of the second statue. She slid down the spiked scimitar of the massive skeleton just as the missiles hit the arm of the plain Minifigure statue. The arm gave way, and the heaving of the Spider Boss’ web caused the arm to be pulled upwards. It punched the Spider Boss with massive force, causing it to tumble down to the bottom on the Monument.<BR />But in the ruckus, the sword held by the plain Minifigure statue slipped from the massive, stone hand, and spiraled up into the sky. <BR />It came down with a thud… and stabbed the Spider Boss through the belly. <BR />The Queen of all Spiders screamed for the last time, the surrounding Spiderlings leaping back in shock. The Spider Boss tried in vain to pull the blade from its body with its four legs, but the stone sword didn’t move.<BR />Then the half of the Monument that consisted of the now almost completely obliterated statue of a bald, plain, new recruit creaked menacingly. First, the head tumbled off, crashing down into the Spider Boss and hurting it even worse.<BR />The head was followed by the whole thing, which fell to the ground, burying the Spider Boss.<BR />“It’s done, then.” Came a voice behind a dumbstruck Madison. “The arachnid is dead. We have thwarted the Darkitect’s plans once again.” <BR />The Space Marauder spun around, and was faced by…<BR />“SILAS! SILAS PENUMBRA!” Madison burst into tears of joy at their victory and the return of the Minifigure, and tackled him in a hug only a person with enough muscle to carry around a Wormholer all day could make. <BR />Lego Universe was saved.<BR /><BR /><BR />AUTHORS NOTE: The Spider Boss has falled. Avant Gardens is saved... well... it isn't until Bob's army is defeated.<BR />But remember, the Darkitects plans are FAR from foiled. </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />What do y'all think about it? <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR />Sorry if it's a bit long <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />~Kahangkrack~ </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />ITS SOOOOO LONG AND INTENESE!!!!!! I BURNS!!!<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR />*I go hide*<BR /><BR />CB</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />LOL. Next chapter coming soon!<BR /><BR />~Kahangkrack~
                
            
			
